    "methodology": "1. Original dataset loaded and target column determined\n2. Dataset split into train (80%) and test (20%) with seed 42 (stratified for classification)\n3. Target column moved to last position (DataPruning convention)\n4. Preprocessing: boolean mapping, NaN imputation, one-hot encoding, label encoding\n5. Train/test feature spaces aligned (intersection of one-hot columns)\n6. DataPruning optimization applied to TRAINING SET ONLY — test set untouched\n7. Safety layer: reduction cap + class preservation (train set only)\n8. Models trained on original train set and optimized train set\n9. Both evaluated on the SAME untouched test set\n10. Delta = Optimized − Original (positive = improvement after optimization)",
